Stage 0 - Linux & BASh Fundamentals

HackBio Internship 2025

Completed command-line exercises and bioinformatics software setup to build foundational Linux and NGS skills.

Project 1 – Bash Basics

- File & directory management (mkdir, mv, rm, ls)
- Downloading and organizing files (wget)
- Text parsing & pattern search (grep, wc)
- Inspecting .fna and .gbk files (sequence, gene names, source organism)
- Terminal management (clear, history)

Project 2 – Bioinformatics Software Setup

- Conda environment creation & activation
- Installed core NGS tools via bioconda: bwa, blast, samtools, bedtools, spades.py, bcftools, fastp, multiqc
- Verified installations (figlet <name>)

Skills Gained

- Linux command-line proficiency
- File handling and sequence parsing
- Conda environment & package management
- NGS workflow preparation
